After I tap out a text to my friend telling her I’m getting there, I’m shocked to find she is actually sending me an in-progress photo of her meal. That is just one of the many things I love about the perils of international travel with Facebook and Instagram.

Sometimes we've all gotta walk for groceries (I miss you, Jo!), but sometimes we like to take the easy way out and just order some Instacart! Head to the real-life farm with these library lady faves!

Sometimes I come home with way too much kale, and I wonder if I can get this place turned into an eco-friendly community. Won’t someone help me to change into comfortable clothes made of sustainable fabrics? Won’t someone offer me sumptuous USA-made vegan desserts? One can’t regret the kale when you’re capping it off with some treats by #BloggerSweetenerAsk!

Wherever you're at in life - personal goals, to-do lists, health-related, you name it - I bet every fabulous fashion babe can appreciate a badly brewed cup 'o Joe. This let's-get-down-to-business collection of coffee book covers should do the trick.
